      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field validation — FDA generic centrifugal pump",
      "description": "Comparison of CFD-predicted velocity fields against particle image velocimetry (PIV) data from the FDA benchmark dataset. RMS error below 8% across all measurement planes at design operating point.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/piv-validation-study-2023",
      "prov:used": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-dataset",
      "uofa:isFoundationalEvidence": false
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/shear-stress-model-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Shear-stress hemolysis sub-model verification against canonical Couette data",
      "description": "The power-law hemolysis sub-model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients) was verified against canonical Couette viscometer data from three independent laboratories. Coefficient of determination R²=0.91 across the calibration range. This result synthesises findings from Giersiepen et al. (1990), Wurzinger et al. (1986), and Zhang et al. (2011) into a unified parameter set used in the CFD solver. The synthesis involved weighted least-squares re-fitting across all three datasets, propagating inter-laboratory variability into expanded coefficient uncertainty bounds. Given the breadth of source material and the rigorous statistical treatment, the synthesised parameter set is considered a robust intermediate evidence node anchoring downstream hemolysis predictions.",
      "uofa:isFoundationalEvidence": false
    }
  ],
