      "name": "Shear-stress hemolysis sub-model verification — multi-study synthesis",
      "description": "This node synthesises findings from Giersiepen et al. (1990), Wurzinger et al. (1986), and Zhang et al. (2011) into a unified power-law coefficient set. Weighted least-squares re-fitting was performed across all three independent laboratory datasets, with expanded uncertainty bounds propagating inter-laboratory variability. The synthesis is considered a robust intermediate evidence node given the breadth of source material, the three-decade span of the underlying experiments, and the consistency of results across fluid dynamic regimes. The parameter set is widely cited in the hemolysis modelling literature and is treated as a well-established intermediate result anchoring downstream CFD hemolysis predictions."
